The paper deals with the approximate degree of Boolean functions, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). It also establishes a connection between approximate degree and quantum Merlin-Arthur (QMA) query complexity, which is a topic in quantum computing (cs.QA). The paper also involves analyzing the complexity of certain problems, such as element distinctness and permutation testing, which are topics in data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper uses techniques from machine learning (cs.LG) to derive some of its results.
